Patterns of Christ throughout Scripture

Introduction: A New Reading
Benefits of this method of reading
	The Scriptures come alive
	God bears witness to Himself through the word
		The word transcends its authors, timeframes, copyists.
	This was always the intent.
Scripture compels this reading
	Gospel “quotations” are actually oblique references
	The road to Emmaus makes Christ the author of this reading
	The Acts record extensive use of this reading
	Hebrews and other epistles use this reading
	This reading compares favorably against the symbolism of Revelation
Elementary prefigures of Christ
	Joseph
	Jonah
Subtle prefigures of Christ
	Judges
	(The Gospel of) Elisha
Prefigures of salvation
	Flood of Noah
	Naaman the Leper
